quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  24,21,"O you who have attained faith, do not follow Satan’s footsteps, for whoever follows Satan’s footsteps<i class=""s"">(should know that) </i>indeed he commands to obscenity and what is deplorable. And were it not for Allah’s grace towards you, and His mercy, not one of you would ever have been purified, ever, but Allah purifies whomever He wills. For Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing."
  24,22,"And let not the ones endowed with grace and affluence swear not to give to the near relatives and the destitute<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>and the emigrants in the way of Allah, and let them pardon and let them overlook. Do you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>not love that Allah should forgive you? For Allah is Oft-Forgiving, Bestowing of mercy."
  24,23,"Those who accuse chaste, unwary, believing women are indeed cursed in the Earlier<i class=""s"">(Life) </i>and the Hereafter, and for them is a great punishment"
  24,24,"on the day when their tongues and their hands and their feet testify against them regarding what they used to do."
  24,25,"On that day, Allah pays them their true recompense in full, and they learn that it is Allah who is the Evident Truth."
  24,26,"Nasty{1}ones are for nasty men, and nasty men are for nasty ones, and good ones are for good men, and good men are for good ones. Those are acquitted of what they say; for them is forgiveness and a noble provision.",footnotes:1:The words ‘nasty’ and ‘good’ are mentioned in feminine form and may refer either to ‘nasty women’ and ‘good women’ or to ‘nasty words and ‘good words’.
  24,27,"O you who have attained faith, do not enter houses other than your own houses until you announce your presence and greet their inhabitants with the greeting of peace. That is better for you, that you may remind yourselves."
